Label: Cbl(cyanocobalamin)
Comment: Cobalamin has been transformed to cyanocobalamin according to lit., before it can undergo conversion by cbLC.

Label: Cbl(cob(II)alamin)
Comment: Should be cob(II)alamin according to literature

Label: 2 * Cbl(cob(III)alamine)
Comment: Compound is suspected to be cob(III)alamine, since reaction with cbLD should produce oxidised form of cob(II)alamin

Label: Cbl(cob(III)alamine)
Comment: Compound is suspected to be cob(III)alamine, since reaction with cbLD should produce oxidised form of cob(II)alamin

Label: Methylcobalamin
Comment: biologically active forms</br>According to enzyme functionallity, becomes [methionine synthase]-cob(II)alamin

Label: HC
Comment: aka haptocorrin or transcobalamin 1</br>Produced in saliva and stomach

Label: IF
Comment: aka (gastric) intrinsic factor, transcobalamin III</br>Located in gastric parietal cells

Label: cbLD
Comment: 'cblD protein might be responsible for branching of the cobalamin metabolism pathways to the cytosolic or mitochondrial compartments' Pubmed: 21114891</br>gene is called MMADHC

Label: cbLE
Comment: Gene is MTRR, protein aka methionine synthase reductase (MSR)</br>reductive regeneration of cob(I)alamin (vitamin B12) cofactor

Label: cbLG
Comment: aka MS or methionine synthase for protein</br>Gene is called MTR, for methyltransferase
